# Room 22 Public Key Cryptography Basics

## Task 1 Introduction

Public key cryptography (asymmetric encryption) ensures authentication, authenticity, integrity, and confidentiality.
Analogy: meeting a business partner → verify identity, confirm words, prevent tampering, maintain privacy.
Digital communication requires the same assurances.
Symmetric encryption = confidentiality; Asymmetric encryption = authentication, integrity, authenticity.
