## Task 3 RSA

RSA enables secure data transmission over insecure channels.
Based on the difficulty of factoring large numbers.
Simplified example:
p = 157, q = 199 → n = 31243.
ϕ(n) = 30888.
e = 163, d = 379.
- Public key = (31243,163).
- Private key = (31243,379).
Message x = 13 → ciphertext y = 16341 → decrypted back to 13.
Real-world RSA uses primes with 300+ digits.
CTFs: variables p, q, n, e, d, m, c.
Tools: RsaCtfTool, rsatool.

